header.gameNote: PAC-12 MEN'S TOURNAMENT PRES. BY NEW YORK LIFE - SEMIFINAL

videos.description: Dylan Ennis with the assist to Tyler Dorsey who hits the three to give Oregon it's first points of the game
videos.headline: Dorsey finally puts Oregon on the board

videos.description: Tyler Dorsey hits the deep three
videos.headline: Dorsey with another three!

videos.description: Jabari Bird goes up to defend a shot and goes down hard, landing on his head. He had to exit to be evaluated for a concussion.
videos.headline: Cal's Jabari Bird lands on his head

videos.description: Don Coleman goes for the layup but is blocked by Chris Boucher
videos.headline: Oregon's Boucher with the big block!

videos.description: Dylan Ennis with the no-look pass to Dorsey who hits another deep three!
videos.headline: Dorsey nails it again!

videos.description: Dylan Ennis makes the smooth layup
videos.headline: Ennis with the layup

videos.description: Grant Mullins hits the jumper to put Cal back on the board
videos.headline: Cal's Mullins ends a streak of little offense

videos.description: Grant Mullins to Charlie Moore for the deep three
videos.headline: Moore for three!

videos.description: Grant Mullins with the turnaround three
videos.headline: Mullins nails another three!

videos.description: Casey Benson to Chris Boucher for the dunk
videos.headline: Boucher with the dunk!

videos.description: Offensive rebound for Cal gives Grant Mullins another chance to nail the three
videos.headline: Cal with another three!

videos.description: Dylan Ennis drives hard for the and-1 with less than :30 left to try and finish the game for Oregon
videos.headline: Ennis hits dagger for Oregon

videos.description: Tyler Dorsey talks about the hard fought win that was this game, being set up well throughout by his teammates and getting excited to play either UCLA or Arizona tomorrow
videos.headline: Postgame Interview with Tyler Dorsey
